## 6. Summary Table of Key Reasons for COVID-19 Vaccine Hesitancy

| Category                      | Specific Reasons                                                                                   | Examples/Notes                                                                                   |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Trust Issues**               | Distrust in government, pharma, health authorities                                               | Historical unethical practices, politicization, conflicting messages                             |
| **Psychological Barriers**     | Fear of needles, anxiety about side effects, pandemic fatigue                                    | Needle phobia (~10% UK hesitancy), fear of unknown long-term effects                            |
| **Perceived Risk**             | Low personal risk perception, complacency                                                       | Younger adults feeling invulnerable                                                             |
| **Information Sources**        | Exposure to misinformation, social media echo chambers                                         | Anti-vaccine content amplification                                                              |
| **Historical Context**         | Legacy of vaccine opposition, medical racism                                                    | Tuskegee study, unethical experiments                                                          |
| **Vaccine-Specific Concerns** | Rapid development, EUA status, mRNA technology, ingredients                                    | Concerns about safety, efficacy, DNA alteration myths                                           |
| **Sociopolitical Factors**     | Political identity, religious/philosophical beliefs                                             | Polarization, religious exemptions                                                              |
| **Social Dynamics**            | Group identity, peer pressure, social exclusion                                                 | Groupthink, social conformity                                                                    |

